{"questionId":"27772","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>In this question you will investigate series of the form</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>q</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mi>q</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>where&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p><strong>and use various methods to find polynomials, in terms of</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></math>, <strong>for such series.</strong></p>\n<p>When&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, the above series is arithmetic.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>You will now consider a method that can be generalized for all values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and consider the following family of functions:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, by applying l’Hôpital’s rule, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to differentiate both the numerator and the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfenced><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>.&nbsp;This form can be used in subsequent work.</p>\n<p><br>(l’Hôpital’s rule applies again since)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong>&nbsp;</em>if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder></math>&nbsp;is not referred to or stated.&nbsp;Subsequent marks are independent of this <em><strong>R</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p><br>attempts to differentiate both the numerator and the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27772","referenceCode":"22N.3.AHL.TZ0.1g.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, by applying l’Hôpital’s rule, show that limx→1f1x=12nn+1.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"g.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.13—Limits and L’Hopitals"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}